n connection rejection.\r\nThere's https://github.com/psychoinformatics-de/ukb_workflow/issues/3 about that (private repo - sorry).\r\n\r\nShort form:\r\nLots of parallel invocations of `create-sibling-ria`. Target considers itself flooded with connections and starts rejecting. We end up with a hanging `git-annex-remote-ora` process, triggered by a call to `git-annex-fsck`. \r\n\r\nRelated: #4436\r\n\r\nI think ultimately this is to be solved by RF'ing ORA special remote and use proper async based runner for the underlying SSH process. Any different effort seems wasted to me. The fundmental issue is the blocking read from stdout of that SSH process. So - push forward #4068 with a more reliable remote execution first.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4437/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/4437/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}